ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The class gave me a substantial grounding in poetry with which I was not familiar, and did not neglect lesser-known works. I can't imagine getting a better grasp of the later Romantics in the time available, and for that the class was invaluable.

Absolutely - it is rare to get the chance to study the collected works of three significant poets in one semester. Paul Fry really knows his stuff, and gave good recommendations for biographies and criticism.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course filled in some major conceptual gaps I had with regard to British Romanticism.
